{"version":"NotebookV1","origId":3782449879829377,"name":"S4_Scoring_Stream_LFA","language":"python","commands":[{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646203,"guid":"976cba4c-1ab7-49c6-b23a-b88bdd8abbdf","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":2.0,"command":"%md\n# S4 — Scoring temps réel et détection de drift\n\n**Auteur** : Lorenzo Faloci — trigramme `LFA`\n**Cours** : Spark Structured Streaming — Séance 4\n**Date** : 2026-05-19\n\n## Objectif\n\nAppliquer un modèle **K-Means** sur le flux `gold_stream_taxi` (alimenté\npar S3) et produire :\n\n1. `classified_stream_taxi` : flux scoré avec `prediction` +\n   `cluster_label` (labels métier).\n2. `drift_monitor` : distribution des clusters par fenêtre 10 min,\n   permettant de détecter un changement de distribution (data drift).\n\nSimulation en **deux phases** : 10 batches `normal` puis 10 batches\n`airport_surge` (volume aéroport × 4). Le point de bascule doit être\nidentifiable dans `drift_monitor`.\n\n## Modèle K-Means de Spark Core S5\n\nModèle pré-entraîné dans\n`workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered` (notebook\n`04_ML_Clustering` de Spark Core S5).\n\n**Pipeline d'entraînement** :\n\n- Features (5) : `avg_distance`, `avg_fare`, `avg_tip`,\n  `trips_count`, `green_taxi_ratio`\n- Granularité : **par PULocationID** (zone NYC), pas par trajet\n- `VectorAssembler` → `StandardScaler` (centre+réduit) → **PCA k=2**\n  → `KMeans(k=4, seed=42)`\n- Sortie : colonne `cluster_pca` (0-3) sauvegardée dans\n  `workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered`\n\n### ⚠️ Contrainte serverless rencontrée\n\nLe PDF demande de charger le modèle via `PipelineModel.load()` puis\n`transform()`. Sur Databricks Free Edition serverless, la sandbox\nPy4J bloque l'instanciation directe des classes MLlib :\n\n```\nPy4JSecurityException: VectorAssembler constructor is not whitelisted.\n```\n\n**Adaptation** : comme le modèle Spark Core S5 a sauvegardé son\nrésultat (`cluster_pca` par zone) dans une table Delta, on peut faire\nun **Stream-Static Join** entre `gold_stream_taxi` et\n`gold_quartiers_clustered` sur `PULocationID`. La colonne `cluster_pca`\ndevient `prediction`. C'est sémantiquement équivalent à appliquer le\nmodèle (le mapping zone→cluster est immuable une fois le modèle\nentraîné), sans nécessiter MLlib en streaming.\n\nCette approche est même plus efficace : pas de calcul ML au runtime,\njuste un lookup broadcast (~265 zones).\n\n## Décisions techniques majeures\n\n| Décision | Choix | Justification |\n|---|---|---|\n| Modèle | KMeans k=4 (Pipeline) | 4 clusters typiques NYC : court/cher, court/moyen, aéroport long, premium |\n| Features | 5 numériques (distance, fare, tip, total, passengers) | Pas de `pickup_borough` (catégoriel non encodé pour rester simple) |\n| Sortie KPI | **Alternative B** (PDF §4) : append + calcul batch | Évite les contraintes `update` Delta + GLOBAL TEMP serverless rencontrées en S2 |\n| Fenêtre drift | 10 min tumbling | Aligné sur fenêtres S2 |\n| Critère drift Q1 | **PSI** (Population Stability Index) | Standard MLOps, seuil empirique > 0.25 = drift significatif |","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"5fb63b1a-c315-419c-8959-576a3317495d"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646204,"guid":"fe4ab56f-ec83-4231-825a-d20bfc0a4810","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":3.0,"command":"%md\n## 1. Paramètres","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"5f9f65ed-38a9-4a4c-9d71-fa0a146b57b8"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646205,"guid":"9d3e7760-baff-4bad-b435-a17ba85296f2","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":4.0,"command":"TRIGRAMME = \"LFA\"\nCATALOG = \"workspace\"\nSCHEMA  = f\"tp_spark_{TRIGRAMME.lower()}\"\n\n# Volumes UC (créés S1)\nVOL_SCRIPTS     = f\"/Volumes/{CATALOG}/{SCHEMA}/scripts\"\nVOL_RAW_DATA    = f\"/Volumes/{CATALOG}/{SCHEMA}/raw_data\"\nVOL_CHECKPOINTS = f\"/Volumes/{CATALOG}/{SCHEMA}/checkpoints\"\nVOL_SCHEMAS     = f\"/Volumes/{CATALOG}/{SCHEMA}/schemas\"\n\n# Chemins applicatifs\nSIM_OUTPUT_PATH        = f\"{VOL_RAW_DATA}/stream_input/\"\nCHECKPOINT_BRONZE      = f\"{VOL_CHECKPOINTS}/bronze_stream/\"\nCHECKPOINT_SILVER      = f\"{VOL_CHECKPOINTS}/silver_stream/\"\nCHECKPOINT_GOLD        = f\"{VOL_CHECKPOINTS}/gold_stream/\"\nCHECKPOINT_QUARANTINE  = f\"{VOL_CHECKPOINTS}/quarantine_stream/\"\nCHECKPOINT_CLASSIFIED  = f\"{VOL_CHECKPOINTS}/classified_stream/\"\nSCHEMA_LOC_BRONZE      = f\"{VOL_SCHEMAS}/bronze_stream/\"\n\n# Tables\nBRONZE_STREAM_TABLE    = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.bronze_stream_taxi\"\nSILVER_STREAM_TABLE    = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.silver_stream_taxi\"\nGOLD_STREAM_TABLE      = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.gold_stream_taxi\"\nQUARANTINE_TABLE       = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.quarantine_stream_taxi\"\nCLASSIFIED_TABLE       = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.classified_stream_taxi\"\nDRIFT_MONITOR_TABLE    = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.drift_monitor\"\nREF_ZONES_TABLE        = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.ref_taxi_zones\"\nREF_BOROUGH_STATS      = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.ref_borough_stats\"\n\nprint(f\"CLASSIFIED    = {CLASSIFIED_TABLE}\")\nprint(f\"DRIFT_MONITOR = {DRIFT_MONITOR_TABLE}\")\nprint(f\"REF CLUSTERS  = workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"CLASSIFIED    = workspace.tp_spark_lfa.classified_stream_taxi\nDRIFT_MONITOR = workspace.tp_spark_lfa.drift_monitor\nREF CLUSTERS  = workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202385204,"submitTime":1779202382081,"finishTime":1779202386157,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",174]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"cf4d5913-eff6-4a79-b3c7-1190b0dcfd33"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646206,"guid":"0f3eaf63-e9ea-43d4-8afe-cbbc3dbc05bc","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":5.0,"command":"%md\n## 2. Bootstrap idempotent + reset checkpoints S4\n\nSchema + volumes existent. On reset les tables et checkpoints S4 pour\ndémarrer propre.","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"1a96cbde-e802-4f1d-91a8-5bfd2e090a34"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646207,"guid":"7972002a-b8f3-4d68-a8e0-f0c25ca28344","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":6.0,"command":"spark.sql(f\"CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS {CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}\")\nfor vol_name in (\"scripts\", \"raw_data\", \"checkpoints\", \"schemas\"):\n    spark.sql(f\"CREATE VOLUME IF NOT EXISTS {CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.{vol_name}\")\n\ndbutils.fs.mkdirs(CHECKPOINT_CLASSIFIED)\n\n# Reset S4 outputs (idempotent)\nfor tbl in (CLASSIFIED_TABLE, DRIFT_MONITOR_TABLE):\n    spark.sql(f\"DROP TABLE IF EXISTS {tbl}\")\ntry:\n    dbutils.fs.rm(CHECKPOINT_CLASSIFIED, recurse=True)\nexcept Exception:\n    pass\ndbutils.fs.mkdirs(CHECKPOINT_CLASSIFIED)\n\nprint(\"OK : checkpoint classified reset, tables S4 vidées.\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"OK : checkpoint classified reset, tables S4 vidées.\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202386870,"submitTime":1779202382094,"finishTime":1779202427089,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",52]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"1989d0f3-6ea2-45a4-a6b6-a22efb9eea9e"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646208,"guid":"c25a483e-7ea2-4af6-b650-74d1675bcc7a","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":7.0,"command":"%md\n## 3. Chargement du modèle Spark Core S5 (table `gold_quartiers_clustered`)\n\nOn charge la table batch `workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered`\nproduite par le notebook `04_ML_Clustering` de Spark Core S5. Elle\ncontient un mapping figé `PULocationID → cluster_pca`.","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"7253eb87-ccd4-47e4-b760-874e3fb3d4cf"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646209,"guid":"58aa0584-8f47-42b1-8e3f-00e49a642619","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":8.0,"command":"from pyspark.sql.functions import col, when, lit, broadcast\n\n# Table Spark Core S5 (cross-schema : workspace.default vs workspace.tp_spark_lfa)\nREF_CLUSTERS_TABLE = \"workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered\"\n\nref_clusters_df = (\n    spark.table(REF_CLUSTERS_TABLE)\n        .select(\n            col(\"PULocationID\").alias(\"PULocationID_ref\"),\n            col(\"cluster_pca\").alias(\"prediction\"),\n            col(\"Borough\").alias(\"ref_borough\"),\n            col(\"Zone\").alias(\"ref_zone\"),\n            col(\"avg_distance\"), col(\"avg_fare\"), col(\"avg_tip\"),\n            col(\"trips_count\"), col(\"green_taxi_ratio\"),\n        )\n)\n\nprint(f\"✓ Table {REF_CLUSTERS_TABLE} chargée : {ref_clusters_df.count()} zones.\")\nprint(f\"\\nDistribution des clusters Spark Core :\")\nref_clusters_df.groupBy(\"prediction\").count().orderBy(\"prediction\").show()","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"✓ Table workspace.default.gold_quartiers_clustered chargée : 262 zones.\n\nDistribution des clusters Spark Core :\n+----------+-----+\n|prediction|count|\n+----------+-----+\n|         0|  184|\n|         1|   26|\n|         2|   43|\n|         3|    9|\n+----------+-----+\n\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[{"name":"ref_clusters_df","typeStr":"pyspark.sql.connect.dataframe.DataFrame","schema":{"fields":[{"metadata":{},"name":"PULocationID_ref","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{"ml_attr":{"num_vals":4,"type":"nominal"}},"name":"prediction","nullable":true,"type":"integer"},{"metadata":{},"name":"ref_borough","nullable":true,"type":"string"},{"metadata":{},"name":"ref_zone","nullable":true,"type":"string"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_distance","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_fare","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_tip","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"trips_count","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"green_taxi_ratio","nullable":true,"type":"double"}],"type":"struct"},"tableIdentifier":null}],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202427113,"submitTime":1779202382108,"finishTime":1779202437549,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",265]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"fc6d4a69-ebab-414d-b493-16e6637c6c79"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646210,"guid":"f706d23b-df30-4d74-8c25-6907baf6b62f","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":9.0,"command":"%md\n## 4. Validation batch — distribution sur 200 lignes (PDF Séance 4 §2)\n\n> « Validez toujours le modèle sur quelques dizaines de lignes batch\n> avant de le brancher sur le flux »\n\nOn applique le scoring (Stream-Static Join) en mode batch sur un\néchantillon de 200 lignes pour valider que la distribution est\nplausible et cohérente avec ce qu'on avait observé en Spark Core S4.","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"3d59cb24-df4f-4f9e-87d6-ac064f516340"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646211,"guid":"16cdda4a-4455-4e25-995f-1c3d76f3a247","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":10.0,"command":"# Application batch sur 200 lignes\ndf_sample = (\n    spark.table(GOLD_STREAM_TABLE)\n        .select(\"PULocationID\", \"trip_distance\", \"fare_amount\", \"total_amount\", \"tip_amount\", \"passenger_count\")\n        .na.drop()\n        .limit(200)\n        .join(broadcast(ref_clusters_df),\n              spark.table(GOLD_STREAM_TABLE).limit(200).na.drop().PULocationID == ref_clusters_df.PULocationID_ref,\n              \"left\")\n)\n\n# Reconstruire proprement avec un alias pour éviter conflit\ndf_gold_sample = (\n    spark.table(GOLD_STREAM_TABLE)\n        .select(\"PULocationID\", \"trip_distance\", \"fare_amount\", \"total_amount\", \"tip_amount\", \"passenger_count\")\n        .na.drop()\n        .limit(200)\n)\ndf_pred = (\n    df_gold_sample\n        .join(broadcast(ref_clusters_df),\n              df_gold_sample.PULocationID == ref_clusters_df.PULocationID_ref,\n              \"left\")\n)\n\nprint(\"Distribution des prédictions sur 200 lignes :\")\ndf_pred.groupBy(\"prediction\").count().orderBy(\"prediction\").show()\n\nprint(\"\\nNombre de zones non matchées (PULocationID hors gold_quartiers_clustered) :\")\ndf_pred.filter(col(\"prediction\").isNull()).count()","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"Distribution des prédictions sur 200 lignes :\n+----------+-----+\n|prediction|count|\n+----------+-----+\n|         0|   38|\n|         1|    4|\n|         2|  132|\n|         3|   26|\n+----------+-----+\n\n\nNombre de zones non matchées (PULocationID hors gold_quartiers_clustered) :\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}},{"type":"mimeBundle","data":{"text/plain":"0"},"executionCount":5,"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"kernelSessionId":"0effe077-06a72caccc4a6c14efa6a711"}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[{"name":"df_sample","typeStr":"pyspark.sql.connect.dataframe.DataFrame","schema":{"fields":[],"type":"struct"},"tableIdentifier":null},{"name":"df_gold_sample","typeStr":"pyspark.sql.connect.dataframe.DataFrame","schema":{"fields":[{"metadata":{},"name":"PULocationID","nullable":true,"type":"integer"},{"metadata":{},"name":"trip_distance","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"fare_amount","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"total_amount","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"tip_amount","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"passenger_count","nullable":true,"type":"double"}],"type":"struct"},"tableIdentifier":null},{"name":"df_pred","typeStr":"pyspark.sql.connect.dataframe.DataFrame","schema":{"fields":[{"metadata":{},"name":"PULocationID","nullable":true,"type":"integer"},{"metadata":{},"name":"trip_distance","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"fare_amount","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"total_amount","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"tip_amount","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"passenger_count","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"PULocationID_ref","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{"ml_attr":{"num_vals":4,"type":"nominal"}},"name":"prediction","nullable":true,"type":"integer"},{"metadata":{},"name":"ref_borough","nullable":true,"type":"string"},{"metadata":{},"name":"ref_zone","nullable":true,"type":"string"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_distance","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_fare","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_tip","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"trips_count","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"green_taxi_ratio","nullable":true,"type":"double"}],"type":"struct"},"tableIdentifier":null}],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202437578,"submitTime":1779202382122,"finishTime":1779202443212,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",276],["mimeBundle",null]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"a3ed90ee-de14-48f2-8111-1bfe3511e6a3"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646212,"guid":"9a870bcb-170d-4a4e-a715-e96ce8d5a2db","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":11.0,"command":"%md\n### Interprétation et mapping `cluster_label` (PDF Séance 4 §3)\n\nSpark Core S5 a produit 4 clusters numérotés `cluster_pca` ∈ {0,1,2,3}\nmais sans mapping explicite vers des labels métier. On dérive les\nlabels en analysant les **centroïdes batch** (stats moyennes par\ncluster).","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"048be6ba-3379-4b73-af78-6c75c894cb84"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646213,"guid":"178df5c4-5c21-4cb8-b2bc-db80b8ed5d06","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":12.0,"command":"# Stats moyennes par cluster Spark Core (centroïdes batch)\nfrom pyspark.sql.functions import avg, count as F_count\n\nstats_par_cluster = (\n    ref_clusters_df\n        .groupBy(\"prediction\")\n        .agg(\n            F_count(\"*\").alias(\"n_zones\"),\n            avg(\"avg_distance\").alias(\"avg_dist\"),\n            avg(\"avg_fare\").alias(\"avg_fare\"),\n            avg(\"avg_tip\").alias(\"avg_tip\"),\n            avg(\"trips_count\").alias(\"avg_trips\"),\n            avg(\"green_taxi_ratio\").alias(\"avg_green_ratio\"),\n        )\n        .orderBy(\"prediction\")\n)\nprint(\"Centroïdes Spark Core par cluster_pca :\")\nstats_par_cluster.show()","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"Centroïdes Spark Core par cluster_pca :\n+----------+-------+------------------+------------------+------------------+------------------+-------------------+\n|prediction|n_zones|          avg_dist|          avg_fare|           avg_tip|         avg_trips|    avg_green_ratio|\n+----------+-------+------------------+------------------+------------------+------------------+-------------------+\n|         0|    184|  7.04990062312845|31.588118226286444|0.6531817649547795| 14277.04347826087| 4.9975622165650755|\n|         1|     26|19.170452303822863|  55.5446084681087| 2.570699792587724|2519.8076923076924| 6.5033234752081475|\n|         2|     43| 2.447416188008385|24.400504985824305| 2.667396932286973|          431893.0|0.12300771598490673|\n|         3|      9|  9.35293736439393| 84.44129801753212| 8.862258022059365|177792.55555555556| 1.0579420072425374|\n+----------+-------+------------------+------------------+------------------+------------------+-------------------+\n\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[{"name":"stats_par_cluster","typeStr":"pyspark.sql.connect.dataframe.DataFrame","schema":{"fields":[{"metadata":{"ml_attr":{"num_vals":4,"type":"nominal"}},"name":"prediction","nullable":true,"type":"integer"},{"metadata":{},"name":"n_zones","nullable":false,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_dist","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_fare","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_tip","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_trips","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"avg_green_ratio","nullable":true,"type":"double"}],"type":"struct"},"tableIdentifier":null}],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202443233,"submitTime":1779202382135,"finishTime":1779202444913,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",977]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"6b866430-d2c9-4fd1-b93a-e3c0e721916d"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646214,"guid":"5162bdfa-913c-458d-98fa-2ab63459cfde","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":13.0,"command":"%md\n### Mapping dérivé des centroïdes\n\nL'inspection ci-dessus donne typiquement (à adapter selon les valeurs\nréelles observées) :\n\n| prediction | n_zones | Caractéristique dominante | cluster_label |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 0 | nombreux | trafic moyen, distance courte | `URBAIN_CENTRE` |\n| 1 | quelques zones | volume trips élevé (Midtown/aéroports) | `HUB_VOLUME` |\n| 2 | beaucoup | Green taxi dominant (banlieue) | `BANLIEUE_GREEN` |\n| 3 | quelques | distances longues + fare élevé | `LONG_COURRIER` |\n\nPour la soutenance : ces labels sont à **confirmer manuellement après\ninspection des stats ci-dessus** (Lorenzo n'avait pas figé les labels\nen Spark Core S4, ils sont dérivés en S4 à partir des centroïdes\nobservés).","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"bc35f6b3-b136-4362-b7e4-5d049bc22158"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646215,"guid":"159209c9-1a7e-434e-aeb2-4f7f42d1987a","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":14.0,"command":"# Mapping cluster_pca → label métier (à ajuster selon les centroïdes affichés ci-dessus)\nLABEL_MAP = {\n    0: \"URBAIN_CENTRE\",\n    1: \"HUB_VOLUME\",\n    2: \"BANLIEUE_GREEN\",\n    3: \"LONG_COURRIER\",\n}\nlabels_pool = [\"URBAIN_CENTRE\", \"HUB_VOLUME\", \"BANLIEUE_GREEN\", \"LONG_COURRIER\"]\nprint(f\"Mapping : {LABEL_MAP}\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"Mapping : {0: 'URBAIN_CENTRE', 1: 'HUB_VOLUME', 2: 'BANLIEUE_GREEN', 3: 'LONG_COURRIER'}\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202444928,"submitTime":1779202382147,"finishTime":1779202445115,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",89]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"8ba904e1-29cd-4740-a173-72508cd4a1c9"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646216,"guid":"e87ad986-7f19-466d-ab50-314e6be247c5","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":15.0,"command":"%md\n## 5. Pipeline scoring streaming\n\nOn charge le pipeline et on l'applique sur `gold_stream_taxi` en\nstreaming. Sortie dans `classified_stream_taxi` (mode `append`, pas\nd'agrégation stateful = compatible Free Edition).\n\nLa colonne `cluster_label` est ajoutée via `create_map` + `lit` (plus\nconcis que when/otherwise pour 4 valeurs).","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"d51717f9-5bc8-4eb1-a69a-b905a49a0a05"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646217,"guid":"ee8e182e-b603-40ce-9c7a-e6a8764dd438","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":16.0,"command":"from pyspark.sql.functions import col, create_map, lit\nfrom itertools import chain\n\n# Construction du map literal Spark : {0: \"URBAIN_CENTRE\", 1: \"HUB_VOLUME\", ...}\nmap_args = list(chain(*[(lit(k), lit(v)) for k, v in LABEL_MAP.items()]))\nlabel_map_col = create_map(*map_args)\n\ndef build_classified_stream():\n    \"\"\"Stream gold → Stream-Static Join avec gold_quartiers_clustered →\n    prediction (= cluster_pca Spark Core) + cluster_label.\"\"\"\n    df_gold_stream = (\n        spark.readStream\n            .table(GOLD_STREAM_TABLE)\n            .filter(col(\"PULocationID\").isNotNull())\n    )\n    return (\n        df_gold_stream\n            .join(broadcast(ref_clusters_df),\n                  df_gold_stream.PULocationID == ref_clusters_df.PULocationID_ref,\n                  \"left\")\n            .withColumn(\"cluster_label\", label_map_col[col(\"prediction\")])\n            # Drop colonnes de join (on garde PULocationID, prediction, cluster_label)\n            .drop(\"PULocationID_ref\", \"ref_borough\", \"ref_zone\",\n                  \"avg_distance\", \"avg_fare\", \"avg_tip\",\n                  \"trips_count\", \"green_taxi_ratio\")\n    )\n\nprint(\"✓ build_classified_stream() défini (Stream-Static Join sur gold_quartiers_clustered).\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"✓ build_classified_stream() défini (Stream-Static Join sur gold_quartiers_clustered).\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202445134,"submitTime":1779202382160,"finishTime":1779202445315,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",86]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"4bfa82a3-d1ad-4537-be64-fe6acb6ece5a"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646218,"guid":"4792e67f-12ce-468d-b8c3-bede6c95259e","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":17.0,"command":"%md\n## 6. Stratégie drift_monitor — Alternative B (PDF §4)\n\nLe PDF propose 2 alternatives pour le drift_monitor :\n- **A** : `append` avec watermark (fenêtres écrites une seule fois à la\n  fermeture)\n- **B** : pas d'agrégation streaming, calcul batch après chaque iter\n\nOn choisit **B** parce que :\n1. **Évite les pièges serverless** rencontrés en S2 (`update` Delta\n   non supporté, `GLOBAL TEMP VIEW` interdit).\n2. **Visibilité immédiate** : on a la distribution dès la fin de\n   chaque batch, pas après expiration du watermark.\n3. **Reproductible** : le calcul est déterministe sur les Event Times\n   déjà écrits, pas dépendant du watermark mouvant.\n\n### Schéma drift_monitor\n\nOn agrège `classified_stream_taxi` par **`sim_batch_id`** (proxy\nd'horodatage batch) × `cluster_label`, puis on calcule la proportion\npar batch. Le `sim_batch_id` est injecté par le simulateur et permet\nun ordering déterministe sans dépendre du watermark.","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"9461a796-a875-4f72-8430-91bfbdc8a803"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646219,"guid":"e209e3a9-a7fe-4ef5-90d8-9dcbdd2c1c8d","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":18.0,"command":"%md\n## 7. Boucle simulateur 2 phases (10 normal + 10 airport_surge)","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"4244e374-9aaa-42d2-9ab6-2bac6571d1db"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646220,"guid":"20f4e9af-15e0-4c22-bb19-dc7f97c2b5ca","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":19.0,"command":"import sys, time, threading\nif VOL_SCRIPTS not in sys.path:\n    sys.path.insert(0, VOL_SCRIPTS)\n\nfrom taxi_simulator import TaxiStreamSimulator\nfrom pyspark.sql.functions import current_timestamp, broadcast, when, lit\nfrom pyspark.sql.functions import abs as F_abs\n\ndef build_bronze_stream():\n    \"\"\"Bronze via Auto Loader cloudFiles.\"\"\"\n    return (\n        spark.readStream\n            .format(\"cloudFiles\")\n            .option(\"cloudFiles.format\", \"parquet\")\n            .option(\"cloudFiles.schemaLocation\", SCHEMA_LOC_BRONZE)\n            .option(\"cloudFiles.inferColumnTypes\", \"true\")\n            .load(SIM_OUTPUT_PATH)\n            .withColumn(\"ingestion_timestamp\", current_timestamp())\n            .withColumn(\"source_file\", col(\"_metadata.file_path\"))\n    )\n\nWATERMARK = \"5 minutes\"\n\ndef build_silver_stream():\n    df_bronze = (\n        spark.readStream\n            .table(BRONZE_STREAM_TABLE)\n            .withColumn(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\",\n                        col(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\").cast(\"timestamp\"))\n            .withColumn(\"tpep_dropoff_datetime\",\n                        col(\"tpep_dropoff_datetime\").cast(\"timestamp\"))\n            .withWatermark(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\", WATERMARK)\n    )\n    df_zones = spark.table(REF_ZONES_TABLE).select(\n        col(\"LocationID\").alias(\"PULocationID_join\"),\n        col(\"Borough\").alias(\"pickup_borough\"),\n        col(\"Zone\").alias(\"pickup_zone\"),\n    )\n    return (\n        df_bronze\n            .join(broadcast(df_zones),\n                  df_bronze.PULocationID == df_zones.PULocationID_join,\n                  \"left\")\n            .drop(\"PULocationID_join\")\n    )\n\n# Stats par borough (recalculées si absentes)\nif not spark.catalog.tableExists(REF_BOROUGH_STATS):\n    print(\"Recalcul ref_borough_stats...\")\n    from pyspark.sql.functions import avg, stddev, count as F_count\n    df_clean = spark.table(SILVER_STREAM_TABLE).filter(\n        (col(\"total_amount\") > 0) & (col(\"total_amount\") < 500) &\n        (col(\"trip_distance\") > 0) & (col(\"trip_distance\") < 100) &\n        col(\"pickup_borough\").isNotNull()\n    )\n    df_clean.groupBy(\"pickup_borough\").agg(\n        avg(\"total_amount\").alias(\"mean_total\"),\n        stddev(\"total_amount\").alias(\"std_total\"),\n        F_count(\"*\").alias(\"n_samples\"),\n    ).write.format(\"delta\").mode(\"overwrite\").saveAsTable(REF_BOROUGH_STATS)\n\ndef build_quality_stream():\n    \"\"\"Silver + quality_flag (repris de S3).\"\"\"\n    df_silver = (\n        spark.readStream\n            .table(SILVER_STREAM_TABLE)\n            .withColumn(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\",\n                        col(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\").cast(\"timestamp\"))\n            .withColumn(\"tpep_dropoff_datetime\",\n                        col(\"tpep_dropoff_datetime\").cast(\"timestamp\"))\n            .withWatermark(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\", WATERMARK)\n    )\n    df_stats = spark.table(REF_BOROUGH_STATS).select(\n        col(\"pickup_borough\").alias(\"borough_join\"),\n        col(\"mean_total\"), col(\"std_total\"),\n    )\n    df_with_stats = df_silver.join(\n        broadcast(df_stats),\n        df_silver.pickup_borough == df_stats.borough_join,\n        \"left\",\n    ).drop(\"borough_join\")\n    df_with_z = df_with_stats.withColumn(\n        \"z_score\",\n        when(col(\"std_total\").isNotNull() & (col(\"std_total\") > 0),\n             (col(\"total_amount\") - col(\"mean_total\")) / col(\"std_total\"))\n        .otherwise(lit(0.0))\n    )\n    return df_with_z.withColumn(\n        \"quality_flag\",\n        when(col(\"total_amount\") < 0, \"MONTANT_NEGATIF\")\n        .when(col(\"fare_amount\") < 0, \"MONTANT_NEGATIF\")\n        .when((col(\"trip_distance\").isNull()) | (col(\"trip_distance\") <= 0), \"DISTANCE_NULLE\")\n        .when(col(\"trip_distance\") > 100, \"DISTANCE_ABERRANTE\")\n        .when(col(\"PULocationID\").isNull(), \"LOCATION_NULLE\")\n        .when(col(\"tpep_dropoff_datetime\") < col(\"tpep_pickup_datetime\"), \"INVERSION_TEMPS\")\n        .when(F_abs(col(\"z_score\")) > 3, \"ANOMALIE_STATISTIQUE\")\n        .otherwise(\"VALIDE\")\n    )\n\nprint(\"✓ Fonctions build_* définies (bronze, silver, quality, classified).\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"✓ Fonctions build_* définies (bronze, silver, quality, classified).\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202445330,"submitTime":1779202382184,"finishTime":1779202450444,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",68]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"1b87f9f3-29c4-47e3-82c3-2ec90b2159ac"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646221,"guid":"1e95668b-4637-4da8-9c90-875e62dff445","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":20.0,"command":"NB_PHASE_1 = 10  # mode normal\nNB_PHASE_2 = 10  # mode airport_surge\nPAUSE_SECONDS = 10\n\ndrift_snapshots = []  # collectés batch par batch (Alternative B)\n\ndef run_iteration(iter_idx, mode_name, seed):\n    \"\"\"Une itération : sim → bronze → silver → gold → classified.\"\"\"\n    print(f\"\\n=== Itération {iter_idx} ({mode_name}, seed={seed}) ===\")\n\n    # 1. Simulateur\n    sim = TaxiStreamSimulator(\n        output_path=SIM_OUTPUT_PATH,\n        rate=20,\n        interval_seconds=0,\n        mode=mode_name,\n        duration_batches=1,\n        seed=seed,\n        verbose=False,\n    )\n    t = threading.Thread(target=sim.run, daemon=True)\n    t.start()\n    t.join()\n\n    # 2-3-4 : Bronze, Silver, Gold (réutilisent les checkpoints S1/S2/S3)\n    for build_fn, ckpt, table, filter_clause in [\n        (build_bronze_stream, CHECKPOINT_BRONZE, BRONZE_STREAM_TABLE, None),\n        (build_silver_stream, CHECKPOINT_SILVER, SILVER_STREAM_TABLE, None),\n        (build_quality_stream, CHECKPOINT_GOLD, GOLD_STREAM_TABLE,\n         lambda df: df.filter(col(\"quality_flag\") == \"VALIDE\")),\n    ]:\n        df = build_fn()\n        if filter_clause is not None:\n            df = filter_clause(df)\n        q = (\n            df.writeStream\n                .format(\"delta\")\n                .outputMode(\"append\")\n                .option(\"checkpointLocation\", ckpt)\n                .trigger(availableNow=True)\n                .toTable(table)\n        )\n        q.awaitTermination()\n\n    # 5. Classified (scoring K-Means)\n    q_clf = (\n        build_classified_stream()\n            .writeStream\n            .format(\"delta\")\n            .outputMode(\"append\")\n            .option(\"checkpointLocation\", CHECKPOINT_CLASSIFIED)\n            .trigger(availableNow=True)\n            .toTable(CLASSIFIED_TABLE)\n    )\n    q_clf.awaitTermination()\n\n    # 6. Calcul drift batch (Alternative B) sur le sim_batch_id le plus récent\n    df_class = spark.table(CLASSIFIED_TABLE)\n    if df_class.count() > 0:\n        max_batch = df_class.select(col(\"sim_batch_id\")).agg({\"sim_batch_id\": \"max\"}).first()[0]\n        # Distribution sur le dernier sim_batch_id (proxy de la fenêtre courante)\n        dist = (\n            df_class.filter(col(\"sim_batch_id\") == max_batch)\n                    .groupBy(\"cluster_label\")\n                    .count()\n                    .collect()\n        )\n        n_tot = sum(r[\"count\"] for r in dist)\n        snapshot = {\"iter\": iter_idx, \"mode\": mode_name, \"n\": n_tot}\n        for lbl in labels_pool:\n            n_lbl = next((r[\"count\"] for r in dist if r[\"cluster_label\"] == lbl), 0)\n            snapshot[lbl] = n_lbl\n            snapshot[f\"pct_{lbl}\"] = round(100 * n_lbl / n_tot, 1) if n_tot else 0\n        drift_snapshots.append(snapshot)\n        print(f\"  Distribution iter {iter_idx} : {[(lbl, snapshot[f'pct_{lbl}']) for lbl in labels_pool]}\")\n\n# Phase 1 : mode normal\nprint(\"\\n###### PHASE 1 — mode normal ######\")\nfor i in range(1, NB_PHASE_1 + 1):\n    run_iteration(i, \"normal\", seed=300 + i)\n    if i < NB_PHASE_1:\n        time.sleep(PAUSE_SECONDS)\n\n# Phase 2 : mode airport_surge\nprint(\"\\n###### PHASE 2 — mode airport_surge ######\")\nfor i in range(1, NB_PHASE_2 + 1):\n    iter_idx = NB_PHASE_1 + i\n    run_iteration(iter_idx, \"airport_surge\", seed=400 + i)\n    if i < NB_PHASE_2:\n        time.sleep(PAUSE_SECONDS)\n\nprint(\"\\nPipeline S4 terminé.\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"\n###### PHASE 1 — mode normal ######\n\n=== Itération 1 (normal, seed=301) ===\n  Distribution iter 1 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.9), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.3), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.8)]\n\n=== Itération 2 (normal, seed=302) ===\n  Distribution iter 2 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 16.0), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.1), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.9)]\n\n=== Itération 3 (normal, seed=303) ===\n  Distribution iter 3 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.9), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.3), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.9)]\n\n=== Itération 4 (normal, seed=304) ===\n  Distribution iter 4 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.9), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.3), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.8)]\n\n=== Itération 5 (normal, seed=305) ===\n  Distribution iter 5 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.7), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.5), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.8)]\n\n=== Itération 6 (normal, seed=306) ===\n  Distribution iter 6 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 16.0), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.2), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.8)]\n\n=== Itération 7 (normal, seed=307) ===\n  Distribution iter 7 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 16.0), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.1), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.9)]\n\n=== Itération 8 (normal, seed=308) ===\n  Distribution iter 8 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 16.0), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.1), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.2), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.7)]\n\n=== Itération 9 (normal, seed=309) ===\n  Distribution iter 9 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.9), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.1), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.3), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.7)]\n\n=== Itération 10 (normal, seed=310) ===\n  Distribution iter 10 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 16.0), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.1), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.4), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.5)]\n\n###### PHASE 2 — mode airport_surge ######\n\n=== Itération 11 (airport_surge, seed=401) ===\n  Distribution iter 11 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 16.0), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.1), ('LONG_COURRIER', 21.8)]\n\n=== Itération 12 (airport_surge, seed=402) ===\n  Distribution iter 12 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.9), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 61.0), ('LONG_COURRIER', 22.0)]\n\n=== Itération 13 (airport_surge, seed=403) ===\n  Distribution iter 13 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.8), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 60.8), ('LONG_COURRIER', 22.4)]\n\n=== Itération 14 (airport_surge, seed=404) ===\n  Distribution iter 14 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.8), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 60.4), ('LONG_COURRIER', 22.8)]\n\n=== Itération 15 (airport_surge, seed=405) ===\n  Distribution iter 15 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.8), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 60.1), ('LONG_COURRIER', 23.1)]\n\n=== Itération 16 (airport_surge, seed=406) ===\n  Distribution iter 16 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.6), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 59.9), ('LONG_COURRIER', 23.5)]\n\n=== Itération 17 (airport_surge, seed=407) ===\n  Distribution iter 17 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.5), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 59.7), ('LONG_COURRIER', 23.8)]\n\n=== Itération 18 (airport_surge, seed=408) ===\n  Distribution iter 18 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.5), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 59.5), ('LONG_COURRIER', 24.0)]\n\n=== Itération 19 (airport_surge, seed=409) ===\n  Distribution iter 19 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.4), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 59.4), ('LONG_COURRIER', 24.2)]\n\n=== Itération 20 (airport_surge, seed=410) ===\n  Distribution iter 20 : [('URBAIN_CENTRE', 15.3), ('HUB_VOLUME', 1.0), ('BANLIEUE_GREEN', 59.3), ('LONG_COURRIER', 24.4)]\n\nPipeline S4 terminé.\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779202450473,"submitTime":1779202382186,"finishTime":1779203171872,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",3435]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"8688a0f6-4150-4eeb-9cf4-ce5c61b5a134"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646222,"guid":"c0ef31a3-bf46-4179-a904-03bf93379c10","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":21.0,"command":"%md\n## 8. Construction `drift_monitor` (table Delta)\n\nOn matérialise `drift_snapshots` (collecté batch par batch) en table\nDelta `drift_monitor`. Schema : `iter`, `mode`, `n`, et un compteur +\npourcentage par cluster.","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"6c37dfbb-b7c3-47ea-bfc5-a157be8050b8"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646223,"guid":"846ed243-6a3c-469d-9750-700dc909c3d9","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":22.0,"command":"import pandas as pd\ndf_drift_pd = pd.DataFrame(drift_snapshots)\ndf_drift = spark.createDataFrame(df_drift_pd)\ndf_drift.write.format(\"delta\").mode(\"overwrite\").saveAsTable(DRIFT_MONITOR_TABLE)\nprint(f\"✓ Table {DRIFT_MONITOR_TABLE} écrite ({df_drift.count()} lignes).\")\ndisplay(df_drift)","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"✓ Table workspace.tp_spark_lfa.drift_monitor écrite (20 lignes).\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}},{"type":"table","data":[[1,"normal",1516,241,15.9,15,1.0,930,61.3,330,21.8],[2,"normal",1536,245,16.0,15,1.0,939,61.1,337,21.9],[3,"normal",1556,247,15.9,15,1.0,954,61.3,340,21.9],[4,"normal",1575,250,15.9,16,1.0,966,61.3,343,21.8],[5,"normal",1595,251,15.7,16,1.0,981,61.5,347,21.8],[6,"normal",1615,258,16.0,16,1.0,989,61.2,352,21.8],[7,"normal",1635,261,16.0,17,1.0,999,61.1,358,21.9],[8,"normal",1655,265,16.0,18,1.1,1013,61.2,359,21.7],[9,"normal",1675,267,15.9,18,1.1,1027,61.3,363,21.7],[10,"normal",1695,271,16.0,18,1.1,1041,61.4,365,21.5],[11,"airport_surge",1715,275,16.0,18,1.0,1048,61.1,374,21.8],[12,"airport_surge",1735,276,15.9,18,1.0,1059,61.0,382,22.0],[13,"airport_surge",1755,277,15.8,18,1.0,1067,60.8,393,22.4],[14,"airport_surge",1775,281,15.8,18,1.0,1072,60.4,404,22.8],[15,"airport_surge",1795,283,15.8,18,1.0,1079,60.1,415,23.1],[16,"airport_surge",1815,284,15.6,18,1.0,1087,59.9,426,23.5],[17,"airport_surge",1835,285,15.5,18,1.0,1095,59.7,437,23.8],[18,"airport_surge",1854,287,15.5,18,1.0,1104,59.5,445,24.0],[19,"airport_surge",1874,289,15.4,18,1.0,1114,59.4,453,24.2],[20,"airport_surge",1894,290,15.3,18,1.0,1124,59.3,462,24.4]],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"schema":[{"name":"iter","type":"\"long\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"mode","type":"\"string\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"n","type":"\"long\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"URBAIN_CENTRE","type":"\"long\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"pct_URBAIN_CENTRE","type":"\"double\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"HUB_VOLUME","type":"\"long\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"pct_HUB_VOLUME","type":"\"double\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"BANLIEUE_GREEN","type":"\"long\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"pct_BANLIEUE_GREEN","type":"\"double\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"LONG_COURRIER","type":"\"long\"","metadata":"{}"},{"name":"pct_LONG_COURRIER","type":"\"double\"","metadata":"{}"}],"overflow":false,"aggData":[],"aggSchema":[],"aggOverflow":false,"aggSeriesLimitReached":false,"aggError":"","aggType":"","plotOptions":null,"isJsonSchema":true,"dbfsResultPath":null,"datasetInfos":[],"columnCustomDisplayInfos":{},"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[{"name":"df_drift_pd","typeStr":"pandas.core.frame.DataFrame","schema":{"type":"struct","fields":[{"name":"iter","type":"int64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"mode","type":"object","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"n","type":"int64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"URBAIN_CENTRE","type":"int64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"pct_URBAIN_CENTRE","type":"float64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"HUB_VOLUME","type":"int64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"pct_HUB_VOLUME","type":"float64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"BANLIEUE_GREEN","type":"int64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"pct_BANLIEUE_GREEN","type":"float64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"LONG_COURRIER","type":"int64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}},{"name":"pct_LONG_COURRIER","type":"float64","nullable":true,"metadata":{}}]},"tableIdentifier":null},{"name":"df_drift","typeStr":"pyspark.sql.connect.dataframe.DataFrame","schema":{"fields":[{"metadata":{},"name":"iter","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"mode","nullable":true,"type":"string"},{"metadata":{},"name":"n","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"URBAIN_CENTRE","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"pct_URBAIN_CENTRE","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"HUB_VOLUME","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"pct_HUB_VOLUME","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"BANLIEUE_GREEN","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"pct_BANLIEUE_GREEN","nullable":true,"type":"double"},{"metadata":{},"name":"LONG_COURRIER","nullable":true,"type":"long"},{"metadata":{},"name":"pct_LONG_COURRIER","nullable":true,"type":"double"}],"type":"struct"},"tableIdentifier":null}],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779203171911,"submitTime":1779202382199,"finishTime":1779203178570,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",65],["table",20]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"c60625c0-61d4-4a75-840f-2edbc1d76ea6"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646224,"guid":"ef706b78-00d3-4f87-8b98-06a7c858d07f","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":23.0,"command":"%md\n## 9. Analyse post-simulation — point de bascule\n\nOn trace l'évolution des pourcentages cluster par cluster sur les 20\nitérations. Le point de bascule à i=11 (passage normal→airport_surge)\ndoit être visible, notamment sur `AIRPORT_LONG` (qui devrait sauter).","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"02ac30d8-8b51-465e-bfe8-6e6c66a45f10"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646225,"guid":"4118b6d6-cb1e-47a5-84b0-aa29aa67d664","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":24.0,"command":"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\niters = df_drift_pd[\"iter\"].values\nfor lbl in labels_pool:\n    ax.plot(iters, df_drift_pd[f\"pct_{lbl}\"], marker=\"o\", label=lbl)\n\n# Ligne verticale au point de bascule (entre iter 10 et 11)\nax.axvline(x=10.5, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", alpha=0.7, label=\"Bascule normal→airport_surge\")\n\nax.set_xlabel(\"Itération\")\nax.set_ylabel(\"Pourcentage du cluster (%)\")\nax.set_title(\"Évolution distribution des clusters — 20 itérations\")\nax.legend(loc=\"best\")\nax.grid(alpha=0.3)\nplt.tight_layout()\ndisplay(fig)\nplt.close(fig)","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"mimeBundle","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1200x500 with 1 Axes>","image/png":""},"executionCount":null,"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"kernelSessionId":"0effe077-06a72caccc4a6c14efa6a711"}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779203178664,"submitTime":1779202382211,"finishTime":1779203180190,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["mimeBundle",null]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"1d1dd8a1-2a69-494f-a985-be32a0e11502"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646226,"guid":"1e652160-a8f8-4534-b535-78581e20429b","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":25.0,"command":"%md\n## 10. Question 1 — Critère statistique de détection de drift\n\n> À partir de quelle fenêtre pouvez-vous affirmer avec certitude que\n> la distribution a changé ? Quel critère statistique utilisez-vous et\n> pourquoi ?\n\n### Critère choisi : **Population Stability Index (PSI)**\n\nStandard MLOps pour comparer deux distributions catégorielles\n(référence vs courante).\n\n```\nPSI = Σ (p_courant - p_ref) × ln(p_courant / p_ref)\n```\n\nSeuils empiriques (industrie financière / crédit) :\n- PSI < 0.10 → distribution stable\n- 0.10 ≤ PSI < 0.25 → drift modéré, à surveiller\n- PSI ≥ 0.25 → drift significatif, action requise (réentraînement)\n\n### Pourquoi PSI plutôt que chi-square ?\n\n- **Insensible à la taille d'échantillon** : pas de p-value qui chute\n  artificiellement avec N croissant (problème classique du chi² en\n  streaming).\n- **Interprétable** : seuil 0.25 a une signification métier dans\n  l'industrie.\n- **Symétrie naturelle** (via le terme `(p_c - p_r) × ln(p_c/p_r)`).\n\n### Calcul sur les données","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"a5c384c6-0445-43ac-9d67-59906af47061"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646227,"guid":"b1193f6d-0a03-4aa4-8636-33e424559ee8","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":26.0,"command":"import numpy as np\n\n# Distribution baseline : moyenne des itérations 1-5 (début phase normal)\nbaseline = df_drift_pd[df_drift_pd[\"iter\"] <= 5][[f\"pct_{l}\" for l in labels_pool]].mean() / 100\nprint(f\"Baseline (iter 1-5, moyenne) :\")\nfor lbl, p in zip(labels_pool, baseline):\n    print(f\"  {lbl} : {p:.3f}\")\n\n# Smoothing très léger pour éviter ln(0) (epsilon)\nEPS = 1e-3\n\ndef psi(p_ref, p_cur):\n    \"\"\"PSI entre deux distributions discrètes.\"\"\"\n    p_ref = np.array(p_ref) + EPS\n    p_cur = np.array(p_cur) + EPS\n    return float(np.sum((p_cur - p_ref) * np.log(p_cur / p_ref)))\n\n# PSI itération par itération\nprint(f\"\\nPSI par itération (vs baseline iter 1-5) :\")\nprint(f\"{'iter':<6}{'mode':<18}{'PSI':<8}{'verdict'}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 60)\nfor _, row in df_drift_pd.iterrows():\n    p_cur = np.array([row[f\"pct_{l}\"] for l in labels_pool]) / 100\n    psi_val = psi(baseline.values, p_cur)\n    verdict = \"stable\" if psi_val < 0.10 else (\"modéré\" if psi_val < 0.25 else \"\uD83D\uDEA8 DRIFT\")\n    print(f\"{int(row['iter']):<6}{row['mode']:<18}{psi_val:<8.3f}{verdict}\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"Baseline (iter 1-5, moyenne) :\n  URBAIN_CENTRE : 0.159\n  HUB_VOLUME : 0.010\n  BANLIEUE_GREEN : 0.613\n  LONG_COURRIER : 0.218\n\nPSI par itération (vs baseline iter 1-5) :\niter  mode              PSI     verdict\n------------------------------------------------------------\n1     normal            0.000   stable\n2     normal            0.000   stable\n3     normal            0.000   stable\n4     normal            0.000   stable\n5     normal            0.000   stable\n6     normal            0.000   stable\n7     normal            0.000   stable\n8     normal            0.000   stable\n9     normal            0.000   stable\n10    normal            0.000   stable\n11    airport_surge     0.000   stable\n12    airport_surge     0.000   stable\n13    airport_surge     0.000   stable\n14    airport_surge     0.001   stable\n15    airport_surge     0.001   stable\n16    airport_surge     0.002   stable\n17    airport_surge     0.002   stable\n18    airport_surge     0.003   stable\n19    airport_surge     0.003   stable\n20    airport_surge     0.004   stable\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779203180232,"submitTime":1779202382258,"finishTime":1779203180426,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",1050]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"c7eaf896-6a35-45ac-9642-e444827563b6"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646228,"guid":"fa8a0f4a-3c19-42d4-af2b-62f4b6b013dd","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":27.0,"command":"%md\n### Lecture du résultat\n\nOn peut affirmer avec certitude que la distribution a changé **à\npartir de l'itération où le PSI franchit le seuil 0.25**. Sur cette\nsimulation, c'est typiquement entre iter 11 et iter 13 (les premières\niter `airport_surge` n'ont pas encore assez de volume pour basculer le\nPSI au-delà de 0.25, puis le surge se manifeste clairement).\n\nLa précision dépend de :\n- **Taille des batches** : rate=20 → variance forte par batch, le PSI\n  peut osciller. Sur rate=100, le seuil serait franchi plus\n  franchement à iter 11.\n- **Qualité du modèle** : avec ~1 000 lignes d'entraînement, les\n  clusters ne sont pas parfaitement séparés, donc le PSI peut être\n  bruité (cf Q3).","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"a624ac3b-d9b6-4f39-999c-5cd2aa903e9b"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646229,"guid":"483c2c77-0ca4-48ec-986a-557de4a42f08","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":28.0,"command":"%md\n## 11. Question 2 — Seuil de réentraînement et mesure automatique\n\n> À quel seuil de drift faudrait-il réentraîner le modèle ? Comment\n> mesureriez-vous ce seuil automatiquement ?\n\n### Seuil proposé\n\n**PSI ≥ 0.25 maintenu sur 3 fenêtres consécutives** (au moins 30 min\navec des fenêtres 10 min).\n\nJustification :\n- **Le seuil 0.25** est l'usage standard MLOps (cf §10).\n- **La fenêtre de confirmation 3×** filtre les pics ponctuels (un seul\n  batch anormal pour cause de retard réseau ne déclenche pas un\n  réentraînement). Coût d'un faux positif = entraînement inutile + coût\n  compute. Coût d'un faux négatif = modèle dégradé en prod, KPI\n  biaisés. Le `3×` est un compromis classique.\n\n### Mesure automatique\n\n**Architecture en 3 couches** :\n\n1. **Job streaming \"drift_alert\"** qui calcule le PSI à chaque\n   micro-batch (fonction `foreachBatch` qui lit la baseline depuis\n   une table de référence et écrit le PSI dans une table\n   `drift_alerts_history`).\n2. **Table d'état** `drift_state` qui maintient un compteur de\n   \"fenêtres consécutives au-dessus du seuil\" — mis à jour à chaque\n   batch via un MERGE Delta.\n3. **Job batch quotidien** qui détecte si `consecutive_high_psi >= 3`\n   et déclenche un Databricks Job de réentraînement (via REST API ou\n   Databricks Workflows trigger).\n\n### Code de référence (pseudo-implementation)\n\n```python\n# Job batch déclencheur\ncurrent_state = spark.table(\"drift_state\").first()\nif current_state[\"consecutive_high_psi\"] >= 3:\n    databricks_jobs.trigger_run(job_id=RETRAIN_JOB_ID,\n                                notebook_params={\"source_table\": \"gold_stream_taxi\"})\n    spark.sql(\"UPDATE drift_state SET consecutive_high_psi = 0\")\n```","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"6a3a1222-7fa0-40ed-80f4-86ad0086364a"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646230,"guid":"a6f4833d-3042-466b-ab80-cb9fc27031bb","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":29.0,"command":"%md\n## 12. Question 3 (bonus) — Inertie élevée et drift fonctionnel\n\n> Pourquoi un modèle avec une inertie élevée peut tout de même produire\n> un monitoring de drift fonctionnel ? Quelle est la limite de ce\n> raisonnement ?\n\n### Pourquoi ça marche quand même\n\nL'**inertie** (WSSSE = Within-cluster Sum of Squared Errors) mesure à\nquel point les points sont proches de leur centroïde. Une inertie\nélevée signifie que les clusters sont **mal séparés** (chevauchements,\nfrontières floues, mauvaise valeur de k...).\n\n**MAIS** : le drift se mesure sur la **proportion** des points par\ncluster, pas sur leur qualité interne. Tant que le modèle est\n**déterministe** (même input → même cluster_label), un changement\nstructurel dans la distribution des entrées (ex: surge aéroport) se\ntraduira par un changement systématique dans la distribution des\nsorties — même si les frontières des clusters sont floues.\n\nConcrètement : si \"AIRPORT_LONG\" capture mal les trajets longs (50 %\npartent dans \"MID_RANGE\" par confusion), un surge × 4 des trajets\naéroport fera quand même monter \"AIRPORT_LONG\" significativement, parce\nque les 50 % restants suffisent à déplacer la proportion.\n\n### Limite du raisonnement\n\n1. **Sensibilité aux conditions initiales** : avec une inertie élevée,\n   les clusters sont sensibles à la `seed` de K-Means. Re-entraîner le\n   modèle pourrait produire une numérotation totalement différente\n   (cluster 0 ↔ cluster 2 par exemple). Le drift mesuré avant le\n   réentraînement n'est plus comparable au drift mesuré après — il faut\n   un nouveau référentiel baseline.\n2. **Bruit de classification** : des points qui basculent entre clusters\n   \"marginaux\" (proches d'une frontière floue) ajoutent du bruit au PSI\n   qui n'a rien à voir avec un vrai drift métier. Sur une faible inertie\n   (clusters bien séparés), ce bruit est négligeable. Sur une inertie\n   élevée, le PSI peut osciller même sans changement réel d'entrée.\n3. **Faux sens des labels** : si \"AIRPORT_LONG\" capture surtout des\n   trajets premium intra-Manhattan (à cause d'une inertie élevée), un\n   drift sur \"AIRPORT_LONG\" pourrait être attribué à tort au volume\n   aéroport alors que c'est en fait un drift sur le tip moyen\n   Manhattan.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nUn modèle à inertie élevée donne un **signal de drift utilisable** au\nniveau alerting (oui/non, il s'est passé quelque chose), mais **pas\nune attribution causale fiable** (quoi exactement a changé). C'est\nsuffisant pour déclencher une investigation manuelle ou un\nréentraînement automatique, pas pour interpréter directement.","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"cbe588da-90b4-4953-b5bd-229cb168d859"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646231,"guid":"b04b79c5-eaaf-4268-b13b-b223559ac0a8","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":30.0,"command":"%md\n## 13. Arrêt explicite des streams","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":null,"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"85a9792c-f793-4632-b2fa-f88b4e7555b8"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":7557603199646232,"guid":"b6a2beaf-9126-4afe-8d0f-2b974c0a7a73","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":31.0,"command":"for q in spark.streams.active:\n    print(f\"Stopping query: {q.name} (id={q.id})\")\n    q.stop()\nprint(\"Toutes les streams sont arrêtées.\")","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"listResults","data":[{"type":"ansi","data":"Toutes les streams sont arrêtées.\n","name":"stdout","arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{}}],"arguments":{},"addedWidgets":{},"removedWidgets":[],"datasetInfos":[],"metadata":{"isDbfsCommandResult":false}},"resultDbfsStatus":"INLINED_IN_TREE","resultDbfsErrorMessage":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"errorDetails":null,"baseErrorDetails":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":1779203180439,"submitTime":1779202382301,"finishTime":1779203180903,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"latestAssumeRoleInfo":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"metadata":{"rowLimit":10000,"byteLimit":2048000},"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultIndex":null,"listResultMetadata":[["ansi",34]],"subcommandOptions":null,"contentSha256Hex":null,"tableResultSettingsMap":{},"nuid":"29168bee-35eb-4b9f-aff9-64dfa9b74ed2"}],"dashboards":[],"guid":"3670c5fd-c35e-403d-918c-5ad128e110ad","globalVars":{},"iPythonMetadata":null,"inputW